Program: Discovery
Title: Eradicating Polio
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03jrwz2
Last Broadcast Date: 22 September 1997
Whether science can eradicate the polio virus. The World Health Organisation has set itself a target of eradicating the polio virus from the planet by 2000. But do scientists know enough to do this? Also in the programme a look at how lead exposure in the womb can rot your teeth and an insight into mosquito man Ronald Ross 100 years after he proved the cause of malaria. Presenter: Martin Redfern. Show less